# 11.6.35.1 Error 37-1 (emergency code 6100h)

# Suggested steps:

Q: What are the suggested steps to address an under-voltage error on the drive?
A1: Restart the device and check if the power supply was switched off.
A2: Verify the actual grid voltage matches the supply setting in parameter PST_VoltageSupply.
A3: Ensure the grid is stable under load conditions.
A4: Check the power supply and restart the device to see if the error persists.
A5: Match the grid voltage with the supply setting and confirm grid stability under load.

A3: Inspect cabling and consider trying another encoder and cable if available.
A4: Review detailed error information for a more in-depth description of the issue.
A5: Ensure encoder setup is correct, including cables and voltage, and consult detailed error info.
